# Upstream reference, kept on disk and deliberately out of version control.
# See NOTICE: we hold no rights to it and cannot redistribute it.
toho-like-js/

# Art-kit output. `bun run art:kit` emits paintable templates here; they are a
# working surface for an artist, regenerated on demand, never committed.
art-kit/

# Imported third-party art pack. `bun tools/import-bulletpack.ts` derives this
# whole tree from a local BulletPack folder whose LICENSE is UNCONFIRMED (no
# license file, no named author). The repo is public, so under CLAUDE.md rule 9
# the ART is not committed — only the importer (tools/import-bulletpack.ts) and
# its mapping (tools/bulletpack-map.json) are. The pack is regenerable on demand.
packs/bulletpack/

# Throwaway measurement harnesses. These drive the real `Run` to answer a
# question a unit test cannot — "does a player ever reach this", "what does
# tier 3 actually deal" — and they are written, read once, and abandoned. What
# survives a probe belongs in a test, not here.
.probe-*.ts
